<div class="container cool-font">

    <div class="row-fluid">
        <h3>SuiMo -> (Suica x Passmo) + BitCoin</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="row-fluid">
        <div class="span6" style="text-align: left">
            <p>Got Bitcoins?  Traveling to Japan? Hate carrying cash?
        </div>
        <div class="span6" style="text-align: right">
          <a href="/info" class="btn btn-primary btn-large">Learn more &raquo;</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row-fluid section1">
        <div class="span12">
            <div class="span3">
                <img class="displayed" id="btcimage" src="https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/8869944/suimo/btc.jpg"/>
                <h3 class="text-center"> pay by bitcoins </h3>
                <p>Visit an exchange (<a href="http://bitcoincharts.com/markets/currency/USD.html">here</a>) to get coins.  Pay us
                    in bitcoin and we will send you a Japanese e-cash card pre-charged with Yen.  Kind of like a debit card ... </p>
            </div>
            <div class="span3">
                <img class="displayed" id="suicapassmo" src="https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/8869944/suimo/suicapassmo.jpg" width="50%" height="50%" />
                <h3 class="text-center">we send you card</h3>
                <p>We ship you the card before you leave.  Please allow time for delivery.  Usually about 2 weeks if sent internationally.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="span3">
                <img class="displayed" src="https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/8869944/suimo/wallet.jpg"/>
                <h3 class="text-center">use card</h3>
                <p>Use the cash card in over thousands of convenience stores, pay for busses, trains, rail station shops, and beyond
                    ... there is not enough room on the website to list all the stores that take Suica or Passmo.  You must discover for yourself.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="span3">
                <img class="displayed" src="https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/8869944/suimo/back.jpg"/>
                <h3 class="text-center">get remainder</h3>
                <p>Done using Suica or Passmo?  Have a left-over balance?  Just send us the card back, and we will refund your balance in
                    Bitcoins. (Inluding the deposit.)</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row-fluid pitch">
        <div class="span6 hidden-phone video-container">

            <iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/qJ_ppLeKAKk" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen=""></iframe>

        </div>
        <div class="span6">
            <div class="thermometer">
                <h2>Suica</h2>
                <p>Japanese e-cash debit card for "Japan Rail" train lines, cabs, buses, stores,
                    and retail shops around any train station.  As of March 31, 2012 there were approximately 177,630
                retail locations around the country.  (<a href="https://www.jreast.co.jp/e/investor/ar/2012/pdf/ar_2012_10.pdf">source</a>)</p>

            </div>
            <br>
            <div class="order">
                <h2>Passmo</h2>
                <p>Japanese e-cash used mostly for private (underground metro) train lines, busses, convinience stores,
                    and countless shops around any train station.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="span8 offset2 social">
                <br>
